The paper is about the mathematical theory of rank-metric codes, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). It also involves the study of codes and their properties, which is related to data structures (cs.DS). The concept of support of a code and its weight enumerators are used, which are topics in signal processing and information retrieval (cs.SI). The paper also discusses duality and q-polymatroids, which are topics in theoretical computer science and combinatorics (cs.CC). Finally, the paper mentions MRD codes and optimal anticodes, which are related to linear algebra and machine learning (cs.LG).
